An R6 class that represents a Localized parameter in an OSP snapshot. A
Localized parameter is a \link{Parameter} identified by its full path within a
target's parameter tree (typically a Simulation or Individual). The path
locates where the override applies.

\code{LocalizedParameter} inherits from \link{Parameter}; everything that works on a
\code{Parameter} also works on a \code{LocalizedParameter}. The only addition is a
required \code{path} field, populated from the \code{Path} element of the raw data.
