\section{Snapshot version assumption}{
\code{osp.snapshots} only supports v11+ snapshots (numeric \code{Version} >= 79); the
check is enforced by \code{Snapshot$new()} at load time. In v11+ snapshots,
path segments named \code{Applications} are migrated to \code{Events}. The migration
runs in \code{initialize()}; for v11+ data it is a no-op because PK-Sim already
uses \code{Events}, and the constructor itself does not re-check the version.
}

\section{Legacy \code{Name} fallback}{
A v11+ snapshot's localized parameter always carries \code{Path}. As a
convenience for hand-rolled data, \code{initialize()} falls back to \code{data$Name}
when \code{data$Path} is missing and emits a deprecation warning so the
substitution is not silent; the resulting object stores the value in
\code{data$Path} and drops \code{data$Name}. Real snapshots never trigger this
branch.
